      "content": "Vitamin K is a key factor in how warfarin works, which is why dietary changes require careful management. However, \"consistent\" intake is tricky because even small fluctuations in spinach or kale can affect your INR levels, making it unpredictable. You should absolutely discuss the idea of dietary adjustments with your prescribing physician, but any changes to your medication dosage must be done under their direct supervision.",
      "source": "target",
