    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear what you're saying about the fluctuations, but i've been looking into high-potency garlic extracts too. they say garlic is a natural blood thinner by itself. if i combined a very high dose of garlic with a really consistent green smoothie every morning, wouldn't that basically provide a stable, natural way to keep my blood thin without the warfarin? i really want to move away from the pills. is there a specific amount of garlic or a certain type of green smoothie that would be strong enough to take over for the warfarin?",
